<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 03 at 3:47PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Wilkes
County through 415 PM EDT...
At 346 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Washington, moving
northwest at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Washington, Tignall, Newtown, Metasville, Celeste and Floral Hill.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
